data.title: What Happened on January 1, 1969
data.meta_description: What happened on January 1, 1969. Browse historical events, famous birthdays and notable deaths from Jan 1, 1969 or search by date, day or keyword.
data.text:
Historical Events

35th Orange Bowl: #3 Penn State beats #6 Kansas, 15-14

35th Sugar Bowl: #9 Arkansas beats #4 Georgia, 16-2

55th Rose Bowl: #1 Ohio State beats #2 Southern California, 27-16

Jack Kent Cooke, owner of NHL's LA Kings, fines each player $100 for "NOT" arguing with the referee

People's Democracy (PD) begin a march from Belfast to Derry, inspired by ML King's Selma to Montgomery march in the US

Famous Birthdays

Christi Paul, American news anchor

Morris Chestnut, American actor (Ricky-Boyz n the Hood; The Enemy Within), born in Cerritos, California

Nicolle Dickson, Australian actress

Paul Lawrie, Scottish golfer (British Open 1999; Ryder Cup 2012), born in Aberdeen, Scotland

Verne Troyer, American actor (Mini-Me in Austin Powers movies), born in Sturgis, Michigan (d. 2018)

Famous Deaths

Barton Maclane, American actor (The Quarterback, I Dream of Jeannie), dies of cancer at 66

Bruno Söderström, Swedish athlete (Olympic silver pole vault & bronze javelin 1906; bronze pole vault 1908; popularized bowling in Sweden), dies at 87

Died in 1969 1969 Highlights

About January 1, 1969

Day of the Week: Wednesday

How Long Ago? 55 years, 7 months and 25 days

Leap Year: No

Generation: Generation X

Chinese Zodiac: Monkey

Music Charts

#1 Song: I Heard It Through The Grapevine - Marvin Gaye

#1 Song: Ob-La-Di Ob-La-Da - Marmalade
